						               													<description>This is actually a 'Variant' for use with the 1965 Version of Avalon Hill's The Battle of the Bulge game. You will have to have the game in order to play this.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 'Variant' components consist of the following: a RULES set of 6-pages plus an 'Errata' sheet; 3-COLOR-Charts; a set of 'counters' which must be cut-apart and glued to 1/2&amp;quot; square pieces prior to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Within the Rules are detailed additions to the 'Tournament' game of 'Bulge-65' with amendments to any of those explained further. Some of these are: Amendment to Zone of Controls-for Combat, Support, &amp;amp; 'Pure'-Armor units; Road Movement-for 'Leg', Motorized, &amp;amp; 'Tracked' units; TAC(Ground Support)-for the Germans; Para-drops-(for the 'von der Heydte' unit); Operation 'GREIF'(the 150th-Pz.Brig.) &amp;amp; the 'Einheit Steilau' Squads; and an Amendment to the Tournament Victory Conditions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Charts included are: one WHITE-with the British Order of Appearance, the Play by Mail Para-drop Results Table(10-Results), the Face to Face Para-drop Results Table(6-Results), with explanations for both; one GREEN-with the German Order of Appearance &amp;amp; Reinforcements; one TAN-with the American Order of Appearance &amp;amp; Reinforcements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game counters are of the following COLOR types: German~'Wehrmacht'-GRAY, Parachute~BLUE, Waffen 'SS'~BLACK, 150th Pz.Brig.&amp;amp; 'E.S.'~1/2-GRAY &amp;amp; TAN; British~RED; &amp;amp; Americans~TAN. The 'NEW' units include: 'Mixed'-Armor; 'Mixed'-Assault Guns; Headquarters; Artillery; Armored-Artillery; Nebelwerfer; Engineers; 'Jagdpanzer'; Tank-Destroyers; Assault Guns; Armored 'Cavalry'; and the 'Special' 150th Pz.Brig. &amp;amp; 'E.S.' Squads.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is an entire 'revamping' of the game and just the 'Fortresses', 'Fortifications(Entrenchments)', &amp;amp; 'Direction' markers are used from the original game. Some of the new concepts involved are the Support Units(HQ &amp;amp; Artillery-ALL kinds), Road movement &amp;amp; Zones of Control for 'Motorized', 'Leg', &amp;amp; 'Armored'('Pure'-Armor &amp;amp; Support Units have NO-Z.O.C.!) units, plus the addition of the British Forces, &amp;amp; the 'Special' German units included.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
